<p>denegate<br />
v. to deny or refuse</p>
<p>In 1873, when the University of Michigan challenged Cornell to the new game of football, Cornell president Andrew D. White declined. He said, &#8220;I will not permit thirty men to travel four hundred miles to agitate a bag of wind.&#8221;</p>
